OL,6,FStaff were "too busy to help"
OL,8,FGreg Rielly, CQC deputy director of
OL,9,Foperations in the Midlands, said: "We
OL,10,Fsaw one person try to stand but was
OL,11,Funsteady on their feet.
OL,13,F"As there weren't any staff around to
OL,14,Fhelp, our inspector had to help them
OL,15,Fto sit back down, or they would have
OL,16,Flikely fallen over. When we brought
OL,17,Fthis up with staff, they said they
OL,18,Fwere too busy to help.
