OL,3,CCare home placed in special measures
OL,4,Cafter 'at risk' residents neglected
OL,6,FMr Rielly said: "We have told Braywood
OL,7,FGardens where we expect to see rapid
OL,8,Fand widespread improvements and will
OL,9,Fcontinue to monitor them closely to
OL,10,Fkeep people safe while this happens.
OL,12,F"We've also told them they can't admit
OL,13,Fany new residents until these
OL,14,Fimprovements are made. We will return
OL,15,Fto check on their progress and won't
OL,16,Fhesitate to take further action if
OL,17,Fpeople are not receiving the care they
OL,18,Fhave a right to expect."
OL,20,F"Immediate and robust plan put in
OL,21,Fplace"
